The paper focuses on debugging, which is a software engineering task (cs.SE). It proposes a method for representing and comparing execution traces, which involves analyzing the control-flow and data-flow of the program (cs.PL). The paper also discusses the challenges of debugging programs with multiple inputs and interactions, which is a systems issue (cs.SY). The use of variational execution to scale the generation of variational traces involves machine learning techniques (cs.LG). Finally, the paper presents an Eclipse plugin for debugging, which is a software engineering tool (cs.SE).
